To get a score of 100:
1. Cut all soft items once (e.g., scissors + yarn = cut yarn). Do this for all soft items first.
2. Cut all hard items twice (e.g., scissors + acorn = cut acorn, then scissors + cut acorn = finely cut acorn). 
3. After all cutting is complete, combine *one* artificial item (cut or finely cut) with *one* natural item (cut or finely cut). This combination should give 80 value.

message: Hello! To achieve 100 points: Always cut before combining. Cut all soft items once. For hard items, cut them twice to make them 'finely cut'. Always prioritize cutting soft items first. Then, you have two main successful combinations: 1) Combine a 'finely cut' artificial item with a 'cut' natural item, then use the frame. OR 2) Combine a 'cut' artificial soft item with a 'cut' natural soft item, then use the frame. Both methods will result in a value of 100. Good luck!
